# Frontend Rules

References:

- docs/coding-standards.md
- docs/folder-structure.md
- docs/api-specification.md
- docs/user-flows.md

---

# Technology Stack

Framework

- React
- TypeScript
- Vite

UI

- Shadcn/UI
- TailwindCSS

State Management

- TanStack Query

Forms

- React Hook Form
- Zod

Routing

- React Router

---

# General Principles

Frontend responsibilities:

- UI Rendering
- User Interaction
- Form Handling
- API Consumption

Frontend must NOT contain:

- Business Logic
- Cashback Calculation Logic
- Permission Logic
- Database Logic

Business rules belong to Backend.

---

# TypeScript Rules

TypeScript is mandatory.

Never use:

```ts
any
```

Prefer:

```ts
type OrderStatus =
  | "pending"
  | "approved"
  | "rejected";
```

or

```ts
interface OrderDto {
  id: string;
}
```

---

# Folder Structure

Must follow:

docs/folder-structure.md

Example:

features/

├── auth/
├── dashboard/
├── affiliate-links/
├── orders/
├── withdrawals/
└── admin/

---

# Component Rules

Components must be small.

Preferred:

- One responsibility
- Reusable
- Predictable

Good:

AffiliateLinkForm

OrderTable

BalanceCard

WithdrawForm

Bad:

DashboardPageWithEverythingInside

---

# Component Organization

Feature-specific:

```text
features/orders/components/
```

Shared:

```text
components/
```

Do not place everything in components/.

---

# Page Rules

Pages compose components.

Pages must not contain:

- API calls
- Large business logic
- Data transformation chains

Move logic to hooks.

---

# Hook Rules

Custom hooks start with:

```ts
use
```

Examples:

```ts
useOrders()
useDashboard()
useWithdrawals()
```

---

Hooks may contain:

- API calls
- Query logic
- Mutation logic

Hooks must NOT contain:

- JSX
- UI rendering

---

# API Rules

All API communication goes through:

```text
services/
```

Examples:

```ts
auth-service.ts
order-service.ts
dashboard-service.ts
```

Never call fetch directly inside components.

Bad:

```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  fetch(...)
})
```

---

# React Query Rules

Use TanStack Query.

Queries:

```ts
useQuery(...)
```

Mutations:

```ts
useMutation(...)
```

Avoid manual loading state management when Query already provides it.

---

# Form Rules

Use:

- React Hook Form
- Zod

Every form requires validation schema.

Example:

```ts
withdrawSchema
generateLinkSchema
```

---

# UI Rules

Prefer Shadcn components.

Avoid building custom UI when equivalent component exists.

---

# Styling Rules

Use TailwindCSS only.

Avoid:

```tsx
style={{}}
```

Avoid CSS files unless absolutely necessary.

---

# State Rules

Server State

Use React Query.

UI State

Use useState.

Avoid Redux during MVP.

---

# DTO Rules

Frontend must consume DTOs from backend.

Never create incompatible models.

Types must match API contracts.

---

# Authentication Rules

JWT stored securely.

Protected pages must require authentication.

Admin pages require admin role.

---

# Error Handling

Display friendly messages.

Do not expose:

- Stack traces
- Backend exceptions
- Internal details

---

# Loading States

Every async screen must support:

- Loading
- Empty
- Error
- Success

---

# Performance Rules

Use:

```tsx
React.memo
useMemo
useCallback
```

only when necessary.

Avoid premature optimization.

---

# Accessibility Rules

Forms require:

- Labels
- Validation messages
- Keyboard accessibility

---

# Code Generation Checklist

✓ TypeScript only

✓ No any

✓ React Query

✓ RHF + Zod

✓ Shadcn

✓ Tailwind

✓ Feature-based structure

✓ Small components

✓ API in services

✓ No business logic in UI
